=====Usage notes=====
* {{q|Mandarin}}
** The tone changes from fourth to second tone when followed by a fourth-tone syllable.
** {{s|not}}
*** The past-perfect form of {{lang|zh|不}} is {{zh-l|沒}} or {{zh-l|未}}, not *{{lang|zh|不了}}.
***: {{zh-x|我 不 當兵。|I am '''not''' becoming a soldier.}}
***: {{zh-x|我 '''沒''' 當兵。|I did '''not''' become a soldier.}}
***: {{zh-x|我 '''未''' 當兵。|I have '''not yet''' become a soldier.}}
***: {{zh-x|我 '''不''' 當兵 '''了'''。|I am '''no longer''' a soldier.}}
***:: Note that the 4th sentence does not mean "I have not become a soldier". Syntactically, {{lang|zh|不}} is a verb prefix that forms a '''stative verb''' with the verb to be negated. Therefore it can not be modified by the perfective aspect marker {{zh-l|了}}, which modifies only '''dynamic verbs'''. When {{lang|zh|了}} appears in a {{lang|zh|不}} sentence, it usually functions as a marker of "currently relevant state" instead.
*** {{lang|zh|不}} can not be used before the verb {{zh-l|有|to have}}. Use {{zh-l|沒}} instead.
***: Incorrect:
***:: {{lang|zh|*我'''不有'''手機。}}
***: Correct:
***:: {{zh-x|我 '''沒有''' 手機。|I do '''not''' have a mobile phone.}}
*** {{lang|zh|不}} can not be used before compounds beginning with {{lang|zh|有}}, or another {{lang|zh|不}}. Depending on the context, other negative particles must be used instead which formally contain a predicate or auxiliary, e.g., {{zh-l|不是}}, {{zh-l|並非}}, imperfective {{zh-l|沒有}}, epistemic {{zh-l|不會}}.
***: Incorrect:
***:: {{lang|zh|*這個問題'''不'''不值一提。}}
***: Correct:
***:: {{zh-x|這 個 問題 '''不是''' 不值 一 提。|This problem is not unworth mentioning.}}
*** The verb can be elided, as in the following:
***: {{zh-x|爲什麼 不 呢？|Why not?}}
**** An equivalent construction is not valid in Cantonese. <!--and other lects?-->
** {{s|can not}}
*** "not" and "can not" are distinguished only by word order.
***: {{zh-x|他 '''不''' 打開 門。|He '''does not''' open the door.}}
***: {{zh-x|他 打 '''不''' 開 門。|He '''can not''' open the door.}}
*** Since {{lang|zh|不}} must be placed before a complement, if there is no complement in the sentence, a placeholder {{zh-l|了|liǎo}} can be used for this purpose.
***: {{zh-x|我 動 不 了{liǎo}。|I '''can not''' move.}}
** {{s|no}} Although {{lang|zh|不}} can be used like English ''no'' to answer a yes/no question, it is more natural to answer it by changing the question to a negative statement.
**: {{zh-x|你 認識 他 嗎？不。|Do you know him? '''No'''.}}
**: {{zh-x|你 認識 他 嗎？( ^我 ) 不 認識。|Do you know him? '''No'''.}}
* When read in {{w|Northern Wu}} languages, such as {{w|Shanghainese}} or [[w:Suzhou dialect|Suzhounese]], the syllable is pronounced the same as {{zh-l|勿|tr=-}}, despite the existing expected pronunciation.

